Documentation
speak(text)
Converts the provided text to speech using the text-to-speech engine.

Parameters:

text (str): The text you want Sabrina to speak.
listen()
Listens to the user's voice input and returns the recognized text.

Returns:

str: Recognized text from the user's speech.
get_weather(city)
Fetches the current weather information for the specified city.

Parameters:

city (str): Name of the city for which to get weather information.
Returns:

str: A description of the weather and temperature in the specified city.
set_reminder(reminder_time, reminder_message)
Sets a reminder that notifies the user at the specified reminder_time with the reminder_message.

Parameters:

reminder_time (str): The time at which the reminder should trigger (in "HH
" format).
reminder_message (str): The message to remind the user.
main()
Main function that continuously listens for user commands and performs actions based on the recognized text.

Running the Code
Replace 'your_api_key' with your actual OpenWeatherMap API key.
Run the script using Python.
This code provides a basic framework for Sabrina. You can expand its functionality by adding more features and improving its natural language processing capabilities.
